metadata.name: Acella Antipyrine and Benzocaine Otic 3 g Solution

clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: Antipyrine is an analgesic often used to test effects of other drugs on liver enzymes In combination with benzocaine in otic solutions antipyrine is indicated for the symptomatic relief of acute otitis media arising from various etiologies

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Antipyrine is an analgesic and antipyretic that has been given by mouth and as ear drops Antipyrine is often used in testing the effects of other drugs or diseases on drug metabolizing enzymes in the liver From Martindale The Extra Pharmacopoeia 30th ed p29
